SIMPLE: defensive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Defensive
<hw>De*fen"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧fensif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Serving to defend or
protect; proper for defense; opposed to <xex>offensive</xex>; <as>as,
<ex>defensive</ex> armor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A moat <qex>defensive</qex> to a house.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Carried on by resisting attack or aggression; --
opposed to <xex>offensive</xex>; <as>as, <ex>defensive</ex>
war</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In a state or posture of defense.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defensive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Defensive
<hw>De*fen"sive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which defends; a
safeguard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wars preventive, upon just fears, are true
<qex>defensives</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>To be on the defensive</b></col>, <col><b>To stand
on the defensive</b></col></mcol>, <cd>to be or stand in a state or
posture of defense or resistance, in opposition to aggression or
attack.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defensively</ent>⟦br⟧
